= One-Page game pitch --- Katana

== Backstory

A boy named Zuni lived with his family in an old Japanese temple. Zuni, who was an only child, lived there with his father and mother who both were samurai warriors.

After the great war in the year 2100, in which both his parents fought, the AI robots won and started taking over the world. Zuni's parents knew that one day the AIs would come to take over their temple, so they started training Zuni to also become a samurai.

The day Zuni turned 13 they arrived. His mother hid Zuni in a garbage bin where he later watched his parents get executed by the AI robots. Then the robots burned the temple to the ground and Zuni kept on hiding for two days straight.

He was so furious and knew that one day he would get revenge. The only thing that survived the fire was his fathers katana. Zuni picked it up with tears in his eyes....

== Gameplay

The game Katana is a difficult, wave-based game in which you play as the main character Zuni.

=== The goal of the game:

The game's goal is to kill the AI robot boss. This is when the game is finished.

=== Raid:
- The player goes on raids to fight enemies. Enemies spawn in waves, with more enemies for every new wave.
- When killing enemies, there is a possibility that they will drop loot, like money, healing items, upgrades, etc.
- When you feel like you can't survive anymore, you can go to your van and extract from the raid. This takes you to your home base (your van).

=== Van:
- In the van view, you are safe. Here you can look in your inventory, fuel up your van to go to new raids, shop different items, and upgrade your van with custom modules, e.g., a turret.

=== Boss:
- To go to the boss, you will have to upgrade your fuel tank (which will require a bit of playtime at least).
- The boss is also difficult, so the player needs to get upgrades to not get killed by it.

== USPs

The main unique selling point of our game is a combination of a wave-based raid game with upgrades and an inventory system, and a Sekiro-esque combat system.

== Target audience

The target audience is people who like the combat in games like sekiro and dark souls but also like the atmosphere of games like cyberpunk. It’s also a game for those who enjoy extraction games like Escape from Tarkov where death might result in a great loss of progression.

== Genre

Action, melee combat, difficulty, extraction, singleplayer and futuristic.

== Hardware platform (e.g. PC or mobile)

We are targeting the PC platform with this game, as this fits best with our combat system and mechanics. It would also be fully possible to add console support down the line.

== Style and aesthetic

The theme is futuristic with Japanese cultural influences. Most of the world will be rundown and overgrown after the robot attack.

== Accessibility issues and solutions

Sensitive controls: The combat system is pretty sensitive to mouse input so if the player has motoric issues it might be a problem. The solution to this is to implement sensitivity sliders.

